\f0\b\fs18 \cf0 View an Individual \'96 Comments\
\b0 \ This screen shows all the staff, general and pastor comments for this individual.\ \ There are three levels of comment privacy:\ \'95 Confidential \'96 can only be viewed by pastors and executive staff members\ \'95 Staff Comments \'96 can be viewed by any ALCF staff member\ \'95 General Comments \'96 can be viewed by anyone with access to the ChMS, including lay ministry leaders\ \ \ \ \ "Posted By" filter will only list the names of users who have posted a comment on this individual.\ \ \ \ \ "Comment Type" filter will be any of the levels of comment privacy that this user is allowed to see.\ \ \ \ \ \ "Edit" is only available for comments that the user has actually entered \'97 no one is able to edit a comment that they didn't enter. Clicking on "Edit" brings up a similar dialog box to that in \b Screen 2.5.1\
\b0 \ "Hide" will hide the comment for all users. It can reappear if the user chooses to "include hidden comments" and then "unhides" the comment.}

\f0\b\fs18 \cf0 View an Individual \'96 Stewardship\
\b0 \ The entire Stewardship section (e.g. everything under 2.6.x including this 2.6 screen) can \i only \i0 be viewed by folks in the Stewardship team. There will be a special permission that is required in order for a user to be able to view anything in this section.\ \ Every stewardship item must be associated with one and \i only \i0 one person. Reports (e.g. reports that can be mailed out to the individual) can be run against individuals or against households.\ \ \ \ Date Range includes things like "View All", "Year to Date", "Month to Date", etc. See any program like Quicken for an example of date ranges to use.\ \ \ \ Funds can be one of the following:\ \'95 Tithes/Offering\ \'95 Building Fund\ \'95 Specific to a Given Ministry\ \'95 Scholarship to a Given Event\ \'95 Support for a given individual or cause\ \ List of specific ministries, events, and individuals or causes can be edited by anyone in the Stewardship committee in the Administration section. See \b Screen ?.? \b0 for more information.\ \ In addition to the set list above, individual campaigns and additional funds can be created by anyone in the Stewardship Committee. Examples of additional funds include:\ \'95 Imagine Campaign\ \'95 ?\ \ \ \ Transaction Types can be one of the following:\ \'95 Cash\ \'95 Check (needs a check #)\ \'95 Credit Card (Online)\ \'95 Credit Card (Recurring)\ \'95 Corporate Match (Pre-Taxed)\ \'95 Corporate Match (Post-Taxed)\ \'95 Stock Donation\ \'95 Car/Automobile\ \'95 ?\ \ Note that any pre-tax Corporate Match contribution should NOT be calculated in receipts used for tax-deductible purposes.\ \ \ \ All transactions also have an internal "notes" or "comments" type of field, which can be edited and viewed only by folks in the Stewardship committee.\ \ \ \ Clicking on any Check # will pop up a graphic with the check image.
